title: Sunflower microgreens
description: Microgreen sunflower seeds produce seedlings that contain about 25% protein.

title: Broccoli Microgreens
description: They are also favored for their health benefits, being a great source of sulforaphane.

title: Pea Seeds
description: Organic pea microgreens are an excellent source of these three protective agents: folate, antioxidants and carotene.

title: Beetroot microgreens
description: Beet microgreens have high levels of Vitamin B6, Vitamin C, Folate, and the minerals copper, iron, magnesium, manganese, and potassium.

title: Parsley Seeds
description: Parsley seed was used traditionally as a carminative to decrease flatulence and colic pain.

title: Cabbage Seeds
description: Cabbage is low in calories and high in fiber. This makes it an excellent option for maintaining a healthy digestive tract.
